pair A, B, C, M;
A = (0, 5.657);
B = (0, 0);
C = (2, 0);
M = 0.5 * A + 0.5 * C;
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(B--M);
label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$M$", M, NE);
label("$4\sqrt{2}$", A--B, W);
label("$2$", B--C, S);
draw(rightanglemark(A,B,C,10));
[/asy] Using the Pythagorean Theorem, we can find $AC^2 = AB^2 + BC^2 = 32 + 4 = 36,$ so $AC = 6.$ Since $\triangle ABC$ is a right triangle, $BM = \frac{1}{2} \cdot AC = \boxed{3}.$

